		<title>
		By: Rodney		</title>
		<link>https://jamesclear.vercel.app/jerry-rice#comment-10024</link>

		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Rodney]]></dc:creator>
		<pubDate>Wed, 09 Jul 2014 04:43:24 +0000</pubDate>
		<guid isPermaLink="false">https://jamesclear-com.uar9g7bv-liquidwebsites.com/?p=5845#comment-10024</guid>

					<description><![CDATA[In reply to &lt;a href=&quot;https://jamesclear.vercel.app/jerry-rice#comment-8304&quot;&gt;Judith Hoch&lt;/a&gt;.

What this says to me is you prefer fame and glory over being a good parent.

If you stop looking at your issue of no time as being a woman only issue, you might see that anyone in that position has similar problems.

I have two kids to look after as well as my elderly parents. I have very little time to myself, which is not nice, but given I have chosen this path I may as well do it as best as I can. It means putting off my wants for another 5 to 7 years, which is also hard at times, and I will find it hard returning to the workforce to gain a high income.

So I decided that my life is not actually about income or even getting recognition at all.

I have my duties to do for now and I work around them where I can, when I can. When my time comes in years to come, I will do them for myself, measuring my success against what I want to achieve rather than stress about the unfairness of the world.

I am a male, similar situation to you, but my outlook to it, compared to yours, are worlds apart.

Accept your situation rather than be annoyed with it.

Do the best you can, when you can, and your time will arrive later... and when it does, just do what you can and only compare against yourself.]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>In reply to <a href="https://jamesclear.vercel.app/jerry-rice#comment-8304">Judith Hoch</a>.</p>
<p>What this says to me is you prefer fame and glory over being a good parent.</p>
<p>If you stop looking at your issue of no time as being a woman only issue, you might see that anyone in that position has similar problems.</p>
<p>I have two kids to look after as well as my elderly parents. I have very little time to myself, which is not nice, but given I have chosen this path I may as well do it as best as I can. It means putting off my wants for another 5 to 7 years, which is also hard at times, and I will find it hard returning to the workforce to gain a high income.</p>
<p>So I decided that my life is not actually about income or even getting recognition at all.</p>
<p>I have my duties to do for now and I work around them where I can, when I can. When my time comes in years to come, I will do them for myself, measuring my success against what I want to achieve rather than stress about the unfairness of the world.</p>
<p>I am a male, similar situation to you, but my outlook to it, compared to yours, are worlds apart.</p>
<p>Accept your situation rather than be annoyed with it.</p>
<p>Do the best you can, when you can, and your time will arrive later&#8230; and when it does, just do what you can and only compare against yourself.</p>
